  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "I am trying to import a node.js package into my `node_modules` directory, and then point the hardhat `paths.sources` field to  that package so that hardhat will compile those contracts. Here is my full `hardhat.config.js`:\r\n```\r\nrequire('@nomiclabs/hardhat-ethers');\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * @type import('hardhat/config').HardhatUserConfig\r\n */\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: {\r\n    version: '0.8.15',\r\n    settings: {\r\n      optimizer: {\r\n        enabled: true,\r\n        runs: 200\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      forking: {\r\n        url: 'https://polygon-mumbai.infura.io/v3/xxxxx'\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  paths: {\r\n    sources: './node_modules/path/to/contracts',\r\n    artifacts: './artifacts'\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, I get the following error when hardhat tries to compile the contracts:\r\n```\r\nHardhatError: HH1006: The file /full/path/to/file.sol is treated as local but is inside a node_modules directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs it possible to point `paths.sources` to a `node_modules` directory? Note that when I copy all of the same contracts from the `node_modules` directory to project root level `./contracts` directory and set `paths.sources: './contracts'`, the compilation runs successfully.",
